Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A large number of pathogens can affect cucurbit crops, which include watermelon (_Citrullus lanatus_); melons and cucumbers (_Cucumis_ spp.); and squashes, gourds, and pumpkins (_Cucurbita_ spp.). The symptoms described above may point to some form of fungal or bacterial rot, but reliable diagnosis of any pathogens affecting the melons will be essential for designing suitable management strategies for the affected farmers. The problems above may also be due to a combination of pathogens and/or other factors.

